channel.description:
Message Dispatch Process of determining which version of a method to execute Java: method signature
(name and argument types) Python: method name only Based on the original object,
not data type Python class Canine: def bark(self) -> None: print("I'm scary")
class Dog(Canine): def bark(self) -> None: print("I'm friendly")
class GuideDog(Dog): def bark(self) -> None: print("I'm helpful")
Java public class Canine { public void bark() { System.out.println("I'm scary"); } }
public class Dog extends Canine { public void bark() { System.out.println("I'm friendly"); } }
public class GuideDog extends Dog { public void bark() { System.out.println("I'm helpful"); } } Message Dispatch Depends on object, not data type
